    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"Fictional\" or \"legend\" sounds like something you'd say to dismiss it, but the weight of this ring and the precision in these letters... it feels too real for just a legend. If it's not in the \"mainstream\" books, then it must have been intentionally erased or kept out of the official history. \n\nLike, if the letters mention a \"Solar Throne,\" there has to be a reason why that specific imagery is used. Can you look deeper? Not just at what people *write* in textbooks, but look at the patterns of lost civilizations or suppressed histories. If Aethelgard was a real power that was eventually absorbed or wiped out, what kind of political or religious structure would a \"Solar Throne\" imply? I need to know if this ring actually represents a legitimate claim to something.",
